Hey everyone! :slightly_smiling_face:
I am retrieving files from Asana via the API and get a URL. I want to use the *HubSpot API: /files/v3/files/import-from-url/async* to upload the file. However, I get the error:

{“status”:“error”,“message”:“*Csrf token is missing from the request*.“,”correlationId”:“e0f54d18-140a-437c-9a22-349d2865f502”,“engagement”:{“hapikey”:“Not engaged, auth is missing”,“service-to-service”:“service-to-service not engaged. Metadata for service-to-service request not found.“,”oauth-token”:“Not engaged, auth is missing”,“internal-cookie”:“internal-cookie not engaged. Cookie not found in the request.“,”app-cookie”:“Engaged”}}

From the response:
*HTTP 202*

{
  “id”: “AAAAEgs9ctY”,
  “links”: {
    “status”: “<https://api-eu1.HubSpot.com/files/v3/files/import-from-url/async/tasks/AAAAEgs9ctY/status>”
  }
}

This indicates that the CSRF token is missing. However, when I send the URL it contains a token. Did somebody experience this before?

Thank you!!

The URL is attached as a screenshot.
